---
name: kie-music
description: Generate music using Suno AI via the kie.ai API. Use when the user asks to generate, create, or make music or background music. Also use when the user invokes /kie-music directly.
---

Generate music via the kie.ai Suno API.

## Step 1 — Parse arguments

The user's args string is the music description (used as `prompt`). Accept these optional flags:
- `--model <version>` — Suno model (default: `V4_5`). Options: `V4`, `V4_5`, `V4_5PLUS`, `V4_5ALL`, `V5`, `V5_5`
- `--style <tags>` — genre/style tags (e.g. `"dark ambient, cinematic"`) — activates custom mode
- `--title <title>` — track title (required in custom mode)
- `--vocals` — include vocals (default is instrumental)
- `--avoid <tags>` — styles to exclude (negativeTags)

### Modes
- **Simple mode** (default): natural-language description as the prompt. Suno generates the music from it.
- **Custom mode** (activated when `--style` is provided): supply explicit style tags for precise control. `--title` should also be provided.

## Step 2 — Check API key

Verify `KIE_API_KEY` is set. If not, tell the user to run: `export KIE_API_KEY=your_key_here`

## Step 3 — Submit the task

**Simple mode:**
```bash
curl -s -X POST https://api.kie.ai/api/v1/generate \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $KIE_API_KEY" \
  -d '{
    "prompt": "<description>",
    "model": "<model>",
    "customMode": false,
    "instrumental": true
  }'
```

**Custom mode** (when `--style` provided):
```bash
curl -s -X POST https://api.kie.ai/api/v1/generate \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $KIE_API_KEY" \
  -d '{
    "prompt": "<description>",
    "style": "<tags>",
    "title": "<title>",
    "model": "<model>",
    "customMode": true,
    "instrumental": true,
    "negativeTags": "<avoid>"
  }'
```

Set `"instrumental": false` only if `--vocals` was passed. Omit `negativeTags` if `--avoid` was not provided. Omit `title` if not provided.

Parse the response. If `code` is not `200`, show `msg` and stop. Extract `data.taskId`.

## Step 4 — Poll for completion

Music generation takes 30–120 seconds. Poll every 10 seconds:

```bash
curl -s "https://api.kie.ai/api/v1/generate/record-info?taskId=<taskId>" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer $KIE_API_KEY"
```

`data.status` values: `PENDING` → `TEXT_SUCCESS` → `FIRST_SUCCESS` → `SUCCESS`
Failure states: `CREATE_TASK_FAILED`, `GENERATE_AUDIO_FAILED`, `SENSITIVE_WORD_ERROR`

Show elapsed time each cycle. If status is a failure state, show `data.errorMessage` and stop.

## Step 5 — Return result

When `status` is `SUCCESS`, extract the audio URL from `data.response.sunoData[0].audioUrl`. If multiple tracks were generated (sunoData may have 2 items), show all URLs.

Display:
- All audio URLs as clickable links, numbered if multiple
- Track title(s) and tags
- Task ID for reference

Ask if the user wants to download locally. If yes, download each:

```bash
curl -L -o ~/Downloads/"music-$(date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S).mp3" "<audio_url>"
```

Report saved paths.
